助教資訊 Contact with Tutor


學習規範 Course Policy
	    Every class is conducted as follows: The instructor (Prof. Wang) will provide a lecture outlining the basic principles of how to critique a paper in the first session of class. He will hand out a paper for such a practice, and the whole class will discuss it on the second class. Then, beginning from the third class, every student is expected to select an article published on an academic journal for all the class to make critique, write a report according to the format privided in this class. Then, the whole class will discuss 1-2 papers each week.Students who select the reading articles must prepare 8-10 slides of background material for all classmates to read to help all students on the critique process. The student who selects the article must lead the discussion and encourage every classmate to contribute his/her opinion.  For the first 7 session, one paper will be discussed for 2 hours, while there will be two papers to be discussed after the 10th session.      

